16 September 2016Minister of Communications Ms Faith Muthambi will deliver a keynote address at the launch of bi-monthly Christian newspaper on Saturday 17th of September 2016 in Krugersdorp, Johannesburg. Currently, the Christian News is circulated in four provinces: Mpumalanga, North West, Limpopo and Gauteng. Next month it will go national. The Government continues to weave a network of support for the community media through grassroots radio, television and independent newspapers. Furthermore, Government through the Ministry of Communications, has a responsibility to revamp and invest in Community Media. This will ensure preservation, production and supply of relevant impactive locally produced programmes. This becomes an opportunity to address burning issues affecting welfare of the society at large , said Muthambi.Details for the Event are as follows: Venue: Silverstar Casino, Krugersdorp Date: Saturday, 17 September 2016 Time: 10: 00 am Enquiries: Mish Molakeng Cell: 082 469 3997 Issued by Government Communications (GCIS) on behalf of the Ministry of Communications